# =============================================================================
# PostgreSQL Service Credentials
# =============================================================================
# DO NOT duplicate secrets here. The root .env is the single source of truth.
#
# All PostgreSQL credentials are defined in the ROOT .env file:
#   /home/patrick/projects/.env
#
# Variables used by shared-postgres:
#   POSTGRES_USER, POSTGRES_PASSWORD, POSTGRES_DB   (superuser)
#   AUTH_DB_USER, AUTH_DB_PASSWORD                   (auth service)
#   L2P_DB_USER, L2P_DB_PASSWORD                    (l2p service)
#   SHOP_DB_USER, SHOP_DB_PASSWORD                  (shop service)
#   VIDEOVAULT_DB_USER, VIDEOVAULT_DB_PASSWORD       (videovault service)
#   ARENA_DB_USER, ARENA_DB_PASSWORD                 (arena service)
#
# To generate a fresh .env with random passwords:
#   cd /home/patrick/projects && ./scripts/generate-env.sh
#
# The PostgreSQL init script (init-databases.sh) reads these from the
# environment at first boot to create per-service databases and users.
# =============================================================================
